HEADWORD: Onychia
<hw>O*nych"i*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Onyx</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A
whitlow.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>An affection of a finger or toe,
attended with ulceration at the base of the nail, and terminating in the
destruction of the nail.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

